<section class="page-hero">
  <div class="breadcrumbs fade-in">
    <a href="/">Home</a><span class="sep">✦</span><a href="/blog/">Blog</a><span class="sep">✦</span><span>Five Habits That Prevent Illness</span>
  </div>
  <span class="overline fade-in">◆ Prevention · Wellness · Dallas–Fort Worth</span>
  <h1 class="page-title fade-in">Five habits that<br><em>actually</em> prevent illness.</h1>
  <p class="page-subtitle fade-in">Evidence-based prevention advice from AymanCare's board-certified primary care physicians, serving Dallas, North Richland Hills, Mesquite, and Valley Ranch.</p>
</section>
<section class="section" style="padding-top: 0; padding-bottom: 100px;">
  <div style="max-width: 780px; margin: 0 auto; font-size: 16px; color: var(--ink-soft); line-height: 1.8;">
    <div class="info-card fade-in" style="margin-bottom: 48px;">
      <div class="l">◆ 01</div>
      <h3 style="font-family: 'DM Serif Display', serif; font-size: 26px; margin-bottom: 12px; font-weight: 400; line-height: 1.2;">Sleep — <em>7 to 9 hours</em> is non-negotiable</h3>
      <p>Sleep is when your immune system repairs and strengthens. Studies consistently show that people who get fewer than 6 hours of sleep are significantly more susceptible to viral infection. Sleep deprivation also raises cortisol, impairs blood sugar regulation, and slows wound healing. No supplement replaces it. If you struggle with sleep quality, mention it at your next visit to AymanCare in Dallas, NRH, Mesquite, or Valley Ranch — it's a medical issue, not a willpower issue.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="info-card fade-in" style="margin-bottom: 48px;">
      <div class="l">◆ 02</div>
      <h3 style="font-family: 'DM Serif Display', serif; font-size: 26px; margin-bottom: 12px; font-weight: 400; line-height: 1.2;"><em>Hydration</em> — especially critical in Dallas summers</h3>
      <p>The general target of 8 cups per day is a starting point — but Dallas's summer heat and DFW's high-activity lifestyle mean most adults need considerably more. Adequate hydration maintains mucosal barriers in the nose and throat (your first line of defense against respiratory viruses during North Texas allergy and cold season), supports kidney function, and keeps blood volume stable. If your urine is darker than pale yellow for most of the day, you're likely under-hydrated.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="info-card fade-in" style="margin-bottom: 48px;">
      <div class="l">◆ 03</div>
      <h3 style="font-family: 'DM Serif Display', serif; font-size: 26px; margin-bottom: 12px; font-weight: 400; line-height: 1.2;"><em>Hand hygiene</em> — still the most effective</h3>
      <p>Handwashing remains the single most evidence-backed intervention for preventing the spread of respiratory and gastrointestinal illness — something our Dallas-area urgent care physicians see firsthand every cold and flu season. The technique matters: 20 seconds with soap, covering all surfaces including between fingers and under nails. Do it after handling public surfaces, before eating, and after being around someone who is sick.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="info-card fade-in" style="margin-bottom: 48px;">
      <div class="l">◆ 04</div>
      <h3 style="font-family: 'DM Serif Display', serif; font-size: 26px; margin-bottom: 12px; font-weight: 400; line-height: 1.2;"><em>Regular movement</em> — even modest activity helps</h3>
      <p>You don't need to be an athlete to get immune benefits from exercise. 30 minutes of moderate activity — a brisk walk, a bike ride, a swim — five days a week improves immune surveillance and reduces chronic inflammation, a contributing factor to nearly every major disease. The Dallas–Fort Worth area offers abundant trails, parks, and recreation facilities. Consistent moderate activity beats sporadic intense exercise. Start where you are and build from there.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="info-card fade-in" style="margin-bottom: 48px;">
      <div class="l">◆ 05</div>
      <h3 style="font-family: 'DM Serif Display', serif; font-size: 26px; margin-bottom: 12px; font-weight: 400; line-height: 1.2;"><em>Annual check-ups</em> at your Dallas primary care doctor</h3>
      <p>The best prevention is catching a problem before it becomes a problem — and most serious conditions develop silently. High blood pressure, elevated cholesterol, prediabetes, thyroid dysfunction, and certain cancers have no symptoms in their early stages. Your annual physical at AymanCare in Dallas TX, North Richland Hills, Mesquite, or Valley Ranch is the one intervention that catches all of them at once. It takes an hour. It could make a decade of difference.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="neighborhood-band fade-in" style="margin-top: 60px;">
      <div>
        <span class="overline" style="color: var(--accent); margin-bottom: 20px; display: block;">✦ Annual physicals in Dallas, TX</span>
        <h2>Book your check-up —<br><em>the best thing</em> you can do.</h2>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p>Most insurance plans cover annual wellness visits at no cost. AymanCare's primary care physicians in Dallas, North Richland Hills, Mesquite, and Valley Ranch (Irving) review your habits, screen for hidden risks, and build a plan with you.</p>
        <div style="display: flex; gap: 12px; flex-wrap: wrap; margin-top: 24px;">
          <a href="/book-online/" class="btn btn-accent">Book appointment →</a>
          <a href="/services/primary-care/" class="btn btn-ghost">Primary care ↗</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
</Base>
